2603:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c **** /**
2604:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  @brief      Enters LP accel motion interrupt mode.
2605:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  The behavior of this feature is very different between the MPU6050 and the
2606:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  MPU6500. Each chip's version of this feature is explained below.
2607:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2608:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n MPU6050:
2609:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n When this mode is first enabled, the hardware captures a single accel
2610:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  sample, and subsequent samples are compared with this one to determine if
2611:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  the device is in motion. Therefore, whenever this "locked" sample needs to
2612:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  be changed, this function must be called again.
2613:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2614:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n The hardware motion threshold can be between 32mg and 8160mg in 32mg
2615:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  increments.
2616:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2617:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n Low-power accel mode supports the following frequencies:
2618:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n 1.25Hz, 5Hz, 20Hz, 40Hz
2619:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2620:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n MPU6500:
2621:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n Unlike the MPU6050 version, the hardware does not "lock in" a reference
2622:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  sample. The hardware monitors the accel data and detects any large change
2623:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  over a short period of time.
2624:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2625:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n The hardware motion threshold can be between 4mg and 1020mg in 4mg
2626:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  increments.
2627:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2628:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n MPU6500 Low-power accel mode supports the following frequencies:
2629:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n 1.25Hz, 2.5Hz, 5Hz, 10Hz, 20Hz, 40Hz, 80Hz, 160Hz, 320Hz, 640Hz
2630:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2631:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n\n NOTES:
2632:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n The driver will round down @e thresh to the nearest supported value if
2633:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  an unsupported threshold is selected.
2634:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n To select a fractional wake-up frequency, round down the value passed to
2635:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  @e lpa_freq.
2636:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n The MPU6500 does not support a delay parameter. If this function is used
2637:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  for the MPU6500, the value passed to @e time will be ignored.
2638:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  \n To disable this mode, set @e lpa_freq to zero. The driver will restore
2639:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  the previous configuration.
2640:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *
2641:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  @param[in]  thresh      Motion threshold in mg.
2642:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  @param[in]  time        Duration in milliseconds that the accel data must
2643:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *                          exceed @e thresh before motion is reported.
2644:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  @param[in]  lpa_freq    Minimum sampling rate, or zero to disable.
2645:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  *  @return     0 if successful.
2646:MyHardWare/eMPL/inv_mpu.c ****  */
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccs1piim.s 			page 200


